    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sept. 849</date>.</p>
          <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>134 Elm St.</placeName></p>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
          <p><persName role="author">G. Middleman</persName></p>
          <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>134 Elm St.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="align(right)"><date>Septr 20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5610</date></p>
			<p>Dear Sir&#47;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I would have <sic>replyd</sic> to<lb/> your request immediately upon knowing you had written but <persName>Mr DeYoung</persName><lb/> only placed your Letter in my possession<lb/> yesterday&#8212;altho he mentioned to one some<lb/> long time since that you had made some<lb/> request for a Book or something &#40;he could not remember&#41; of me.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>which he would inform me of<del>f</del><lb/> In respect to the Letter&#44; you wish<lb/> of me <persName>Mr Middleman&#39;s</persName> Letter will<lb/> explain&#8212;I have some other matter<lb/> to communicate to you which I will<lb/> attend to immediately after <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> in the mean time receive my<lb/> best wishes for your happiness<lb/> and believe me to be yours<lb/> sincerely&#8212;<persName role="author">Ansel Leo</persName></p>
			<p>If you wish to publish <persName>Mr<lb/> Middleman&#39;s</persName> Letter I must request<lb/> you will do so without extracting<lb/> <hi rend="underline">one word</hi> from the original<lb/> otherwise neither he nor I wish<lb/> to see it in print</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author"><hi rend="underline">AL</hi></persName></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>&#38;c &#38;c &#38;c</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><hi rend="underline">private</hi></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>371&#8212;Walnut St</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p><add><hi rend="underline">Hebrew</hi></add> <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> <date>Sept 20&#44; 1849</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>134 Elm St.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(11)"><addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. Leo</persName> has indeed shown me your<lb/> letter&#44; asking that he send you the letter of<lb/> the Rabbi of <placeName>Warsaw</placeName>&#44; and <del>from</del> the Bette Din<lb/> with regard to the law of the &#42;<hi rend="underline">Get</hi> which was sent by<lb/> post. This letter was sent by the Rabbi<lb/> and the court of <placeName>Warsaw</placeName> to the undersigned<lb/> at the address of <persName>Rev. Mr. Leo.</persName> I was the one<lb/> who arranged this <hi rend="underline">Get</hi> and sent it by post<lb/> to <placeName>Warsaw</placeName>&#44; but God forbid that I should<lb/> be the cause for the stumbling of many by<lb/> having this letter translated into English<lb/> and published in the &#8220;Occident&#44;&#8221; so that every<lb/> wicked and <add>&#63;</add>fulous man who never<lb/> studied and doesn&#39;t know what to do<lb/> with a <hi rend="underline">Get</hi> of this sort&#44; nor even with an<lb/> ordinary <hi rend="underline">Get</hi>&#44; hearing that a <hi rend="underline">Get</hi> of this<lb/> kind was written will pride himself by<lb/> paying. &#8220;I&#44; too&#44; can do so&#44;&#8221; and he<lb/> will send a <hi rend="underline">Get</hi> from a husband to his wife.<lb/> The fact is that legally this woman<lb/> who asked for a divorce is still</p>
			<p>&#42;Bill of Divorce</p>
		<pb n="5"/>
			<p>married and has never been divorced&#44;<lb/> because the one who arranged the<lb/> divorce&#44; knows nothing about the law<lb/> governing such cases. That is why I<lb/> refrain from sending you this letter to<lb/> publish in the &#8220;Occident&#8221;&#44; for I have no<lb/> desire that evil should come through you<lb/> and a stumbling block for <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; so<lb/> that through me <del>illegitimate<add>&#63;</add></del><lb/> illegitimacy should increase <del>through<lb/> me</del>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Your friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Godol Middleman</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
